        <h1>Drew Branson</h1>
        <div class="section">
            <h2 class="section-title">Bio</h2>
            <p>Drew Branson is a geospatial analyst with a Master of Applied Science in Geophysics and Geodesy from Queen's University. He has experience in a variety of fields, including geospatial analysis, UAV surveys, and permafrost research. He is also a certified drone pilot and has experience in scripting languages such as Python, R, and Powershell.</p>
            <h2>Education</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Master of Applied Science in Geological Engineering (Geophysics and Geodesy): Queen's University, 2022</li>
                <li>Bachelor of Applied Science in Geological Engineering: Queen's University, 2018</li>
            </ul>
            <h2>Experience</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Geospatial Analyst: TRE Altamira, 2021-present</li>
                <li>Field Manager: Pioneer Exploration, 2020-2021</li>
                <li>Research Assistant: Geophysics and Geodesy lab, Queen's University, 2017-2020</li>
                <li>Permafrost Research Assistant: Geological Survey of Canada, 2018</li>
                <li>Park Warden: Ontario Ministry of Natural Resources and Forestry, 2016-2017</li>
                <li>Canoe Tripping Guide: Camp Pathfinder, 2012-2015</li>
            </ul>
            <h2>Skills</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>ArcGIS, ArcGIS Pro, QGIS</li>
                <li>UAV surveying</li>
                <li>Project management</li>
                <li>Scripting (Python, R, Powershell, BASH)</li>
            </ul>
            <h2>Contact</h2>
